cs.GT, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.MA 

The paper deals with a multi-agent game theory problem, specifically a general-sum differential game, which is a subfield of game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves navigation, which suggests that it could fall under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes a framework for resolving ambiguity between equilibria, which involves reasoning and inference, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The state evolves in continuous time, which suggests that it could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses simulations, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
